ğŸ”¹ How to Remember AWS & Azure CLI Categories
1. Think Like a Cloud Architecture Diagram
Every cloud workload usually has these building blocks:

Compute â†’ Where apps run (VMs, containers, functions)
Storage â†’ Where data is stored (S3/Blob, disks)
Network â†’ How things connect (VPC/VNet, subnets, firewalls)
Database â†’ Specialized storage (RDS/SQL, DynamoDB/CosmosDB)
Identity & Access â†’ Who can do what (IAM/Azure AD, roles, policies)
Monitoring â†’ Logs, metrics, alerts (CloudWatch/Azure Monitor)
Management â†’ Resource groups/stacks, accounts, billing
---------------------------------
2. Mnemonic Trick (C-S-N-D-I-M-M)
Remember categories in this order:

ğŸ”¹ Compute
ğŸ”¹ Storage
ğŸ”¹ Network
ğŸ”¹ Database
ğŸ”¹ Identity
ğŸ”¹ Monitoring
ğŸ”¹ Management

ğŸ‘‰ Mnemonic: â€œCloud Services Need Daily Integrated Managed Monitoringâ€

